<section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>The <code>data-range</code> attribute enhances a native <code>&lt;input type="range"&gt;</code> with cross-browser styling, an optional value bubble, prefix/suffix formatting, and tick markers. This is a combined page covering <code>data-range</code>, <code>data-bubble</code>, and <code>data-markers</code>.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/examples/demos/range-basic.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/range"
      title="Range Slider"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Basic range slider">{{ basicCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-range</code> to any <code>&lt;input type="range"&gt;</code>. The init script:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Wraps the input in a <code>.range-wrapper</code> div for layout control</li>
      <li>Normalizes cross-browser track and thumb styling via <code>appearance: none</code></li>
      <li>Sets a <code>--range-pct</code> CSS custom property (0&ndash;100%) on every <code>input</code> event</li>
      <li>If <code>data-bubble</code> is present, creates an <code>&lt;output&gt;</code> element positioned above the thumb</li>
      <li>If <code>data-markers</code> is present, renders tick marks along the track based on the <code>step</code> attribute</li>
      <li>If a <code>&lt;datalist&gt;</code> is linked via <code>list</code>, renders labeled tick marks from the option elements</li>
    </ol>
    <p>The underlying input remains a real form control. It submits with the form and fires native <code>input</code> and <code>change</code> events.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Attributes</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-range</code></td>
          <td>boolean</td>
          <td>Enables cross-browser range styling and the <code>--range-pct</code> custom property.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-bubble</code></td>
          <td>boolean</td>
          <td>Shows a floating value bubble above the thumb that updates on input.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-prefix</code></td>
          <td>string</td>
          <td>Text prepended to the bubble value (e.g., <code>"$"</code>).</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-suffix</code></td>
          <td>string</td>
          <td>Text appended to the bubble value (e.g., <code>"%"</code>, <code>"&deg;"</code>).</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-markers</code></td>
          <td>boolean</td>
          <td>Renders tick marks along the track at each <code>step</code> interval.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-range-init</code></td>
          <td>boolean</td>
          <td>Set automatically to prevent double-binding. Do not set manually.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Value Bubble</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-bubble</code> to display a floating value readout above the thumb. The bubble tracks the thumb position and updates in real time as the user drags.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <layout-stack data-layout-gap="l">
        <div>
          <label for="brightness-demo">Brightness</label>
          <input type="range" id="brightness-demo" data-range data-bubble min="0" max="100" value="75">
        </div>
      </layout-stack>
    </div>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Range with value bubble">{{ bubbleCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Prefix and Suffix</h2>
    <p>Use <code>data-prefix</code> and <code>data-suffix</code> to format the bubble value. The prefix appears before the number and the suffix after it.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <layout-stack data-layout-gap="l">
        <div>
          <label for="price-demo">Price</label>
          <input type="range" id="price-demo" data-range data-bubble data-prefix="$" min="0" max="500" value="150">
        </div>
        <div>
          <label for="opacity-demo">Opacity</label>
          <input type="range" id="opacity-demo" data-range data-bubble data-suffix="%" min="0" max="100" value="80">
        </div>
      </layout-stack>
    </div>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Prefix and suffix formatting">{{ prefixSuffixCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Tick Markers</h2>
    <p>Add <code>data-markers</code> to render tick marks along the track. Ticks are generated at each <code>step</code> interval between <code>min</code> and <code>max</code>.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <div>
        <label for="temp-demo">Temperature</label>
        <input type="range" id="temp-demo" data-range data-bubble data-markers data-suffix="&deg;" min="60" max="90" step="5" value="72">
      </div>
    </div>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Range with tick markers">{{ markersCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Datalist Labels</h2>
    <p>Link a <code>&lt;datalist&gt;</code> via the native <code>list</code> attribute to render labeled tick marks. Each <code>&lt;option&gt;</code> in the datalist becomes a labeled marker on the track.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <div>
        <label for="rating-demo">Rating</label>
        <input type="range" id="rating-demo" data-range data-bubble min="1" max="5" step="1" value="3" list="rating-labels-demo">
        <datalist id="rating-labels-demo">
          <option value="1" label="Poor"></option>
          <option value="2" label="Fair"></option>
          <option value="3" label="Good"></option>
          <option value="4" label="Great"></option>
          <option value="5" label="Excellent"></option>
        </datalist>
      </div>
    </div>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Range with datalist labels">{{ datalistCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

