  <section>
    <h2>CSS Custom Property</h2>
    <p>The <code>--range-pct</code> custom property is set on the input element and updated on every <code>input</code> event. Its value ranges from <code>0%</code> to <code>100%</code>, representing the thumb position relative to the track. Use it for filled-track effects or other dynamic styling.</p>

    <code-block language="css" show-lines label="Using --range-pct for a filled track">{{ cssVarCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>DOM Structure</h2>
    <p>After initialization, the following DOM structure is created:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>.range-wrapper</code> &mdash; layout container wrapping the input</li>
      <li><code>&lt;output for="inputId"&gt;</code> &mdash; the value bubble (only with <code>data-bubble</code>)</li>
      <li><code>.range-markers</code> &mdash; tick mark container (only with <code>data-markers</code>)</li>
      <li><code>.range-labels</code> &mdash; label container (only with a linked <code>&lt;datalist&gt;</code>)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Styling</h2>
    <p>The track and thumb are fully customizable via CSS custom properties. All styles are gated on <code>[data-range-init]</code> so the input renders normally without JavaScript.</p>

    <code-block language="css" show-lines label="CSS custom properties">{{ stylingCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Dynamic Elements</h2>
    <p>Range inputs added to the DOM after page load are automatically enhanced via a MutationObserver. No manual initialization is needed.</p>

    <code-block language="javascript" show-lines label="Dynamically added range inputs">{{ dynamicCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The <code>&lt;output for="inputId"&gt;</code> element semantically links the bubble to the input for screen readers</li>
      <li>Native keyboard support is preserved &mdash; arrow keys adjust the value, Home/End jump to min/max</li>
      <li>A visible <code>&lt;label&gt;</code> is required for the input</li>
      <li>Tick labels from <code>&lt;datalist&gt;</code> provide additional context for sighted users</li>
      <li><code>prefers-reduced-motion</code>: bubble transitions are disabled when reduced motion is preferred</li>
      <li>Without JavaScript, the range input renders as a standard browser slider &mdash; progressive enhancement</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
